# Salesforce Integration

## Architecture

The Customer Management use case implements bidirectional sync between MuleSoft Object Store and Salesforce:

- `customer-papi` (Process API) orchestrates sync operations
- `customer-sf-sapi` (System API) connects to Salesforce via Salesforce Connector
- `customer-mock-service` simulates Salesforce responses for local dev

## Data Mapping: Customer <-> SF Account

| Customer Field | SF Account Field | Notes |
|---------------|-----------------|-------|
| id | Id | SF Id is 18-char, local is UUID |
| firstName | FirstName | From Account or Contact |
| lastName | LastName | From Contact (linked to Account) |
| email | PersonEmail or Contact.Email | Depends on Account type |
| phone | Phone | |
| company | Name | Account Name |
| status | Active__c or custom | May need custom field |
| syncId | Id | SF record ID stored for correlation |

## Salesforce Connector Config

- Authentication: Username-Password OAuth flow
- Properties in config YAML:
  - `sf.username`, `sf.password`, `sf.securityToken`
  - `sf.url` (login endpoint)
- For local dev, `config-local.yaml` points `sf.host` to the mock service (port 8084)

## SF CLI Usage (Dashboard Backend)

The backend uses Salesforce CLI (`sf`) for org management:
- `sf org display` -- get org info
- `sf data query --query "SOQL"` -- run queries
- `sf org login password` -- authenticate

Credentials are stored in the encrypted vault under category "salesforce".

## Sync Logic (Process API)

- **To Salesforce**: reads customers from Object Store, upserts into SF Account via sf-sapi
- **From Salesforce**: queries SF Accounts via sf-sapi, upserts into Object Store
- Conflict resolution: last-write-wins based on updatedAt timestamp
- Audit trail: every sync operation logged to a dedicated Object Store
